but they had the same percussion teacher.


254
0:19:20,52 --> 0:19:23,52
I hate your mum and I hate you.


255
0:19:23,52 --> 0:19:29,8
That's brilliant. Brilliant !


256
0:19:29,8 --> 0:19:33,8
- Vulva, hi.
- Brian ! You came !


257
0:19:33,8 --> 0:19:37,8
- Wouldn't have missed it for the world.
- Are you still painting ?


258
0:19:37,8 --> 0:19:40,68
Not exclusively.
I'm moving into multimedia pastures -


259
0:19:40,68 --> 0:19:45,88
installations, a platter of organic processes
mixed with a pinch of irony


260
0:19:45,88 --> 0:19:48,76
and a side helping of self-deprecation.


261
0:19:48,76 --> 0:19:51,4
Sounds delicious !


262
0:19:51,4 --> 0:20:5,64
You should see what's for pudding.


263
0:20:5,64 --> 0:20:8,0
Oh, Brian, you came.


264
0:20:8,0 --> 0:20:9,84
No, I just spilt my drink.


265
0:20:9,84 --> 0:20:13,36
So nice to see you. Are you still painting ?


266
0:20:13,36 --> 0:20:16,56
N-not... er,... multimedia,...


267
0:20:16,56 --> 0:20:21,24
platters,... irony and self-deprecation.


268
0:20:21,24 --> 0:20:23,92
Sounds a little hard to swallow.


269
0:20:23,92 --> 0:20:25,72
There's... there's pudding.


270
0:20:25,72 --> 0:20:29,48
Pud-ding ! I always loved your quirkiness.


271
0:20:29,48 --> 0:20:32,56
You must be able to see I've moved on.


272
0:20:32,56 --> 0:20:35,8
The projects I've been working on
with Hoover


273
0:20:35,8 --> 0:20:38,0
