- This is Hoover.


287
0:21:34,44 --> 0:21:36,76
Bye.


288
0:21:36,76 --> 0:21:39,2
Bye, then.


289
0:21:39,2 --> 0:21:49,48
I'll see you later.


290
0:21:49,48 --> 0:21:53,16
- So beautiful.
- Yeah.


291
0:21:53,16 --> 0:21:57,6
Like a... kind of visual poetry.


292
0:21:57,6 --> 0:22:1,12
- Wish I could do that.
- Well, I'm sure you could if you had funding.


293
0:22:1,12 --> 0:22:4,44
Right hook... bang.


294
0:22:4,44 --> 0:22:7,48
- What ?
- I should have done it long ago, Daisy ?


295
0:22:7,48 --> 0:22:12,36
In his drunken, childish way, Tim saved me.


296
0:22:12,36 --> 0:22:17,32
Talk about expression, talk about the truth,


297
0:22:17,32 --> 0:22:23,92
but what truer expression is there
than the purity of the clenched fist ?


298
0:22:23,92 --> 0:22:27,24
I am a man, Daisy.


299
0:22:27,24 --> 0:22:29,32
A man !


300
0:22:29,32 --> 0:22:32,16
<i>Vulva treated me like a monkey !</i>


301
0:22:32,16 --> 0:22:35,36
I'm more than that, I am a man !


302
0:22:35,36 --> 0:22:37,64
A monkey-man !


303
0:22:37,64 --> 0:22:41,84
A beast with a mind, and a mind, and fists !


304
0:22:41,84 --> 0:22:48,92
And I will not be subdued again,
not by Vulva, not by anyone !


305
0:22:48,92 --> 0:23:3,72
Hey, fella !


306
0:23:3,72 --> 0:23:6,56
Morning, slugger. Any letters ?


307
0:23:6,56 --> 0:23:8,92
I don't know.


308
0:23:8,92 --> 0:23:13,88
Agh !


309
0:23:13,88 --> 0:23:16,32
- How do you feel ?
- Oh, like I'm gonna die.


310
0:23:16,32 --> 0:23:19,64
- Oh, me too.
- So what happened last night ?


311
0:23:19,64 --> 0:23:23,16
We went to see
an interesting piece of contemporary theatre,


312
0:23:23,16 --> 0:23:27,32
<i>we drank an enormous amount of free wine,
we ate our body weight in Twiglets</i>


313
0:23:27,32 --> 0:23:29,88
